#: ../../unittesting.md:0
msgid "Write and run automated unit tests for Solidity smart contracts in Remix IDE using the built-in Solidity Unit Testing plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:0
msgid "solidity unit testing, remix testing, smart contract tests, assert, remix ide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:8
msgid "Solidity Unit Testing Plugin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:10
msgid "The Solidity Unit Testing plugin allows you to write and run automated tests for your Solidity smart contracts to verify they work correctly before deployment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:12
msgid "It helps you generate test files, write test functions using a built-in assertion library (like `Assert.equal`, `Assert.notEqual`), and execute those tests in a separate environment to see pass/fail results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:14
msgid "Activating the Solidity Unit Testing Plugin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:16
msgid "To activate the plugin, go to the Plugin Manager, search \"Unit Testing\" and enable the \"Solidity Unit Testing\" plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:20
msgid "When the plugin loads, you’ll see a screen like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:22
msgid "![Unit testing page](images/unit-testing/a-unit-testing-feature.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:22
msgid "Unit testing page"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:24
msgid "Test directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:26
msgid "When you load the plugin, you need to specify a directory where the plugin will load and store test files. By default, it's a **tests** folder at the root of your Workspace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:29
msgid "The plugin will not automatically create directories. You must click \"Create\" to generate the specified folder structure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:33
msgid "After specifying the test folder, click the \"**Create**\" button. Alternatively, you can select an existing folder as the **tests** folder by typing \"/\" followed by the name of the folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:35
msgid "![Test Directory](images/unit-testing/a-unit-testing-test-directory.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:35
msgid "Test Directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:37
msgid "Generating Tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:39
msgid "The plugin can generate generic test files that contain information about developing tests for a contract. The name of the generic test file is determined by the currently active `.sol` file on the Main Panel. If there is no active file, a generic test file named, **newFile_test.sol** will be created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:41
msgid "Below is an example of a generic test file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:87
msgid "Writing Tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:89
msgid "Write sufficient unit tests to ensure that your contract works as expected under different scenarios."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:91
msgid "Remix injects a built-in **assert** library for testing. You can visit the library documentation {doc}`here </assert_library>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:93
msgid "Additionally, Remix allows the usage of special functions in the test file to make testing more structural. They are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:95
msgid "`beforeEach()` - Runs before each test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:96
msgid "`beforeAll()` - Runs before all tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:97
msgid "`afterEach()` - Runs after each test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:98
msgid "`afterAll()` - Runs after all tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:100
msgid "To get started, see {ref}`this simple example <unittesting_examples:1. Simple example>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:103
msgid "You can use {doc}`RemixAI </ai>` to generate tests for your files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:107
msgid "Running Tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:109
msgid "Once you are done with writing tests, select the file(s) and click on `Run` to execute the tests. The execution will run in a separate environment. After completing the execution of one file, a test summary will be shown:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:111
msgid "![](images/unit-testing/a-unit-testing-run-result.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:113
msgid "For failed tests, there will be more assertion details to analyze the issue. Clicking on failed test will highlight the relevant line of code in the editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:115
msgid "Stopping Tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:117
msgid "If you have selected multiple files to run the tests and want to stop the execution, click on `Stop` button. It will stop execution after running the tests for current file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:119
msgid "Customizing Tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:121
msgid "Remix facilitates users with various types of customizations to test a contract properly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:123
msgid "1. Custom Compiler Context"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:125
msgid "Solidity Unit Testing refers to the Solidity Compiler plugin for compiler configurations. Configure `Compiler`, `EVM Version`, `Enable Optimization` & `runs` in the Solidity Compiler plugin and this will be used in the Solidity Unit Testing plugin for contract compilation before running unit tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:127
msgid "![](images/unit-testing/a-unit-testing-custom-compiler-config.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:129
msgid "2. Custom Transaction Context"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:131
msgid "For interacting with a contract's method, the main parameters of a transaction are `from` address, `value` & `gas`. Typically, a method's behaviour is tested with different values of these parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:133
msgid "One can input custom values for `msg.sender` & `msg.value` of transaction using NatSpec comments, like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:144
msgid "Instructions to use:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:146
msgid "Parameters must be defined in the method's NatSpec"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:147
msgid "Each parameter key should be prefixed with a hash (**#**) and end with a colon following a space (**:&nbsp;**) like `#sender: ` & `#value: `"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:148
msgid "For now, customization is only available for parameters `sender` & `value`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:149
msgid "Sender is the `from` address of a transaction which is accessed using `msg.sender` inside a contract method. It should be defined in a fixed format as '**account-**<account_index>'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:150
msgid "`<account_index>` varies from `0-2` before remix-ide release v0.10.0 and `0-9` afterwards"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:151
msgid "**remix_accounts.sol** must be imported in your test file to use custom `sender`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:152
msgid "Value is `value` sent along with a transaction in `wei` which is accessed using `msg.value` inside a contract method. It should be a number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:154
msgid "Regarding `gas`, Remix estimates the required gas for each transaction internally. Still if a contract deployment fails with `Out-of-Gas` error, it tries to redeploy it by doubling the gas. Deployment failing with double gas will show error: `contract deployment failed after trying twice: The contract code couldn't be stored, please check your gas limit`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:156
msgid "Various test examples can be seen in [examples](https://remix-ide.readthedocs.io/en/latest/unittesting_examples.html) section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:158
msgid "Points to Remember"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:160
msgid "A test contract cannot have a method with parameters. Having one such method will show error: `Method 'methodname' can not have parameters inside a test contract`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:161
msgid "Number of test accounts are `3` before remix-ide release v0.10.0 and `10` afterwards"
msgstr ""

#: ../../unittesting.md:162
msgid "While a test file which imports **remix_accounts.sol** might not compile successfully with Solidity Compiler plugin, do not worry, this will have no bearing on its success with Solidity Unit Testing plugin."
msgstr ""
